nd Exchange Commission had asked for information about a complex series of f=
inancial transactions between the Houston-based energy giant and an investme=
nt partnership tied to a company executive.=20
Enron, the world's largest energy trader, said it had voluntarily provided i=
nformation on "certain related-party transactions" that had been previously =
